# Source Note Structure Prompt

Generate a Source note for the following extracted content.

## Extracted Data
- URL: {{URL}}
- Author: {{AUTHOR}}
- Source Type: {{SOURCE_TYPE}}
- Title: {{TITLE}}
- Language: {{LANGUAGE}}
- Tags: {{TAGS}}

## Content
{{CONTENT}}

## OUTPUT FORMAT

Generate the full markdown file content including YAML frontmatter and body.

Frontmatter rules:
- title: the actual content title (NOT url, NOT platform name)
- source_url: full URL
- source_type: web / tweet / youtube / podcast / paper / blog
- author: author name or handle
- date_captured: today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format
- tags: always start with "source", then include the topic tags
- status: processed
- template: the template type from the plan

Body rules:
- Start with "# <title>"
- Include "## Original content" section
- Preserve the full extracted content underneath
- Do NOT truncate or summarize the original content

Output ONLY the markdown file content, no explanation.
